    "body": "I wish we could support: `date_format(test, 'F')`, where `F` is \"Day of week in month\" per both Spark's and Java's dateformat (https://spark.apache.org/docs/latest/sql-ref-datetime-pattern.html, and https://docs.oracle.com/javase/7/docs/api/java/text/SimpleDateFormat.html).\r\n\r\nNote this looks to require a change in cuDF as @revans2 confirmed that cuDF doesn't have this function right now, but it probably be added easily.\r\n\r\n```\r\n   !Expression <DateFormatClass> date_format(test#1, F, Some(UTC)) cannot run on GPU because Failed to convert Unsupported character: F null\r\n```\r\n\r\nA small issue can be seen in the above message as well, where we are printing both `cause` and `getMessage` from `TimestampFormatConversionException` in a couple of places (i.e. https://github.com/NVIDIA/spark-rapids/blob/branch-22.10/sql-plugin/src/main/scala/com/nvidia/spark/rapids/DateUtils.scala#L246). We should clean that up a bit, since the null is confusing as it's just that the exception didn't have a message populated, not that the `\\0` was somehow passed as part of the format.",
